cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with recognizing human actions in video data. The use of weights assigned to different body parts also suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories may be relevant. Additionally, the use of video data suggests that multimedia (cs.MM) may also be relevant. Finally, the focus on human perception and recognition suggests that human-computer interaction (cs.HC) may also be relevant.
